Search about Mariadb Image in dockerhub 
1. run a container from it || add this option to the docker run command --env MARIADB_ROOT_PASSWORD=my-secret-pw 
2. name the container <yourname>-maridadb
3. portforward port 3306 from the host to the same port inside the container
4. make sure that the container runs in the detached mode
5. Create account in Dockerhub
6. run a second container from the same image
7. list the running containers
8. Search how to get the default port the service inside the container is listening on 
9. Do that in the mariadb and send screenshot
